cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SD 

This paper deals with the problem of modelling shapes and drawings, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and computer graphics (cs.GR). The use of probabilistic models and inference methods suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the use of Monte Carlo methods and Approximate Bayesian Computation suggests a possible connection to statistical computing (cs.SD).
